article.headline: KENTUCKY 80, (24) FLORIDA 65
article.story:
GAINESVILLE, Florida (Ticker) -- Jenny Pfeiffer scored 23 
points and Jennifer Humphrey grabbed 19 rebounds as Kentucky
posted a 80-65 victory over No. 24 Florida in a Southeastern
Conference matchup.

Pfeiffer found her rhythm from the floor, making 6-of-9
3-pointers.  She helped the Wildcats go 9-of-24 overall from the
arc.

While Humphrey was a force in the paint, the Wildcats also
received a big effort from Eleia Roddy, who pulled down 14
rebounds.  The duo helped Kentucky to a 55-39 advantage on the
glass.

Carly Ormerod added 16 points and Samantha Mahoney 13 for the
Wildcats (12-3, 2-1 SEC), who held a 35-33 lead at halftime
before pulling away over the final 20 minutes.

Dalila Eshe scored 23 points and Brittany Davis 15 for Florida
(13-3, 1-2), which shot just 32 percent (22-of-68) - including a
woeful 1-of-13 from the arc - in its second straight loss.
